# changelog

## 2026-06-12

- Hardened initialization quality contracts with structured MonitoringPolicy coverage gates, objection dedupe/resolution metadata, centralized required-output schema registration, node-specific tool allowlists with invented-tool evidence audit, A2 retrieval quality checks, LangSmith/business acceptance audit metadata, and prompt resource hygiene linting.

## 2026-06-07

- Configured LangSmith MCP server in `.mcp.json` with both `langsmith-hosted` (via Render endpoint with `LANGSMITH-API-KEY` header) and `langsmith-local` (via `uvx langsmith-mcp-server` command with local environment variables).

## 2026-06-03

- Added a local read-only Brief State debug viewer with a stdlib HTTP server, Supabase/Postgres run querying, document 1/document 2 review pages, and per-agent ReAct loop/tool/delegation/objection metrics.
- Added debug viewer view-model tests covering global research, expectation units, ReAct audit aggregation, missing audit handling, and secret redaction for rendered API payloads.
- Improved LangSmith trace readability with dynamic per-call run names, a local Custom Output Rendering page, and unified Simplified Chinese human-readable LLM output rules while preserving structured JSON contracts.
- Hardened the local LangSmith renderer endpoint for browser iframe loading with no-store responses, CORS/private-network preflight headers, and README troubleshooting notes for localhost and HTTPS tunnel usage.
- Suppressed expected local debug viewer client-disconnect noise, so browser refreshes, iframe reloads, and aborted JSON responses no longer print WinError 10053 tracebacks.
- Reworked the LangSmith Custom Renderer into a raw-first recursive JSON viewer that always displays metadata, metadata.inputs, outputs/data, and complete postMessage payloads before adding optional DoxAgent AgentResult/provider-response summaries.
- Made LangSmith run names monotonic per blackboard run/agent/workflow node by assigning a gateway-level `langsmith_loop_index`, and stopped real API smoke tests from forcing memory storage so Supabase-backed runs can appear in the Brief State Viewer.
- Reworked free-tier market-data tools by removing Alpha Vantage daily OHLCV and FMP press releases, adding Twelve Data daily OHLCV plus yfinance daily fallback, normalizing Tavily search depth, constraining FMP sector-performance parameters, and adding light SEC/FRED rate limiting with real smoke coverage.

## 2026-06-01

- Separated prompt and skill injection into file-backed system/agent/workflow prompt blocks, DoxAgent-owned internal task skills, and migrated external skill packages under `prompts/`.
- Added `doxagent.prompts` with `PromptRegistry`, `PromptInjectionPolicy`, `PromptInjector`, `PromptAssembler`, `PromptBundle`, and assembled prompt metadata for runtime audit visibility.
- Updated `AgentRuntimeConfig` and agent runners to use prompt block ids, internal task skill ids, external skill package ids, and `AgentTask.prompt_bundle` while keeping `skill_bundle` for external-package compatibility.
- Narrowed `SkillRegistry` and `SkillInjector` to external skill packages so internal SOPs and system prompts are no longer managed as skills.
- Added documentation in `dev_plan/PROMPT_SKILL_SEPARATION_PLAN.md` and README explaining the three prompt/skill categories and non-code prompt editing workflow.
- Implemented Post-MVP 3.7/3.8 O1/A1/A2 realization contracts with `TaskType.DELEGATED_RETRIEVAL`, `ExpectationConstructionResult`, `DoxAtlasAuditResult`, `DelegatedRetrievalResult`, `DelegatedRetrievalRequest`, and `create_a2_retrieval_delegation(...)`.
- Repositioned A2 as a Tavily-only delegated retrieval and fact-check agent, limiting its default tool permissions to `tavily.search` and `tavily.extract` while preserving the internal `A2` agent id.
- Added O1 expectation-construction, A1 DoxAtlas-audit, and A2 Tavily retrieval skills plus mock Tavily tools for offline default tests.
- Wired `ResolveObjectionsAndDelegations` in `agent_runner` mode to call A2 for blocking delegations, write retrieval results to Working Memory, complete delegations only with sufficient evidence, and route remaining objections back to O1 resolution.
- Added tests covering A2 Tavily-only permissions, delegation helper exposure, mock Tavily evidence conversion, A2 blocker recovery, and insufficient-evidence blocking behavior, plus documentation in `dev_plan/PHASE_3_7_3_8_O1_A1_A2_REALIZATION.md`.
- Added the default ReAct agent harness for autonomous in-agent tool/delegation loops, including max-step enforcement, Scratchpad audit, per-tool call limits, similar-query warnings, concurrent-safe tool execution, bounded context compaction, and compatibility switches for single-shot and caller-planned tool execution.
- Added ToolRegistry descriptors for model-facing allowed-tool metadata and tests covering ReAct default behavior, legacy execution modes, tool limits, similarity warnings, permission failures, delegation guards, compaction, and concurrent tool execution.
- Switched initialization `agent_runner` defaults to the DashScope Bailian Responses API (`qwen3.6-flash`) with real tool registry construction, local DashScope settings, and reasoning-summary audit capture.
- Reworked `BuildGlobalResearch` in `agent_runner` mode to call C1/C2/C3/O4/O1 through the agent runner, require O1 to use only `doxa_get_narrative_report`, and assemble document 1 without the previous pending market-narrative placeholder.
- Added ReAct/workflow final-payload validation for `ResearchSection`, `ExpectationConstructionResult`, `DoxAtlasAuditResult`, and `DelegatedRetrievalResult`, plus stricter document 2 expectation-patch validation requiring 1-3 valid evidenced `ExpectationUnitDocument` patches.
- Disabled mock blocker auto-resolution in `agent_runner` mode, moved A2 retrieval hints to ReAct tool requirements, and added gated Phase 17 real initialization smoke tests for document 1/document 2.
- Tightened the P1 real-tool/review path: production defaults now use Bailian plus the real registry, all real tools expose stronger descriptors, A1 uses only low-level DoxAtlas read tools, ReviewExpectationFields runs A1/C1/C3/O4, O1 objection resolution requires revised patches or rejection evidence, and the mock blocker backdoor is disabled in `agent_runner`.
- Completed LangSmith tracing wiring for the default Bailian path by loading `.env` LangSmith settings into the SDK environment, wrapping Bailian's OpenAI-compatible client, attaching task/ReAct metadata through tracing context, and normalizing local `.env` / `.env.example` LangSmith entries.

## 2026-05-31

- Implemented Post-MVP 3.2 real ToolRegistry integration with explicit real-tool registry construction, provider settings, normalized tool errors, in-memory TTL caching, DoxAtlas HTTP tool clients, SEC/FRED/BLS/BEA/Fed/Polymarket/Alpha/FMP/Finnhub/Tavily/yfinance tool clients, and agent permission updates while preserving mock-first defaults.
- Added Phase 3.2 real-tool contract tests and marked free-tier smoke tests behind `DOXAGENT_RUN_REAL_API_TESTS=1` so normal test runs remain offline and quota-safe.
- Added real provider environment placeholders plus `yfinance` and `websockets` dependencies for HK-only yfinance snapshots and bounded Finnhub trade-stream capture.
- Split the Phase 3.2 real tool implementation into `tools/factory.py` and per-provider modules under `tools/providers/`, while keeping `tools/real.py` as a compatibility export layer for existing imports.
- Tightened DoxAtlas real tool configuration against `DOXATLAS_TOOL_SCHEMAS.md`, including per-endpoint payload validation, DoxAtlas error-envelope mapping, alias endpoint checks, and read-only default agent authorization for run tools.
- Expanded Phase 3.2 real API smoke coverage to exercise every non-DoxAtlas provider/tool individually with content-level availability assertions, and added Alpha Vantage request spacing for free-tier multi-call tools.

## 2026-05-29

- Added `dev_plan/DEVELOPMENT_PLAN.md` with a phased development plan based on `dev_plan/PRD.md`, including architecture boundaries, MVP order, core module rollout, stabilization, and final external-agent adapter integration strategy.
- Created `dev_plan/DEVELOPMENT_PLAN.md` in the workspace with a detailed phased plan from PRD requirements; noted that external GitHub agent analysis and adapter work must happen only after the core DoxAgent contracts, Blackboard service, workflow, and validation layers are stable.
- Implemented the Phase 0 project baseline: Python 3.11 `uv` configuration, `src/doxagent` package skeleton, baseline tests, local environment template, README setup instructions, Phase 0 boundary document, and mock-first external capability policy.
- Narrowed the Phase 0 Microsoft Agent Framework dependency to `agent-framework-core>=1.6,<2` after the all-in-one `agent-framework` meta package pulled optional Azure integrations that failed dependency resolution and exceeded the minimal-runtime scope.
- Added explicit Ruff exclusions for `.uv-cache`, `.venv`, and external reference sources so workspace-wide linting checks only DoxAgent-owned code and tests.
- Implemented Phase 1 domain contracts with Pydantic models for AgentTask, AgentResult, BlackboardPatch, EvidenceRef, Objection, Delegation, Commit Log entries, Working Memory entries, Belief State snapshots, and the five PRD work document schemas.
- Added Phase 1 stateless promotion-blocking helpers plus contract fixtures and tests covering required fields, JSON round trips, evidence source types, and objection/delegation blocking behavior.
- Added `dev_plan/PHASE1_CONTRACTS.md` and README notes documenting the schema boundary, ID strategy, structured document field strategy, and Phase 1 non-goals.
- Implemented Phase 2 Model Gateway contracts and async client boundary, including standard request/response models, normalized gateway errors, usage and audit summaries, mock client, OpenAI and Anthropic SDK adapters, JSON response normalization, retry/fallback orchestration, and centralized LangSmith provider wrapping.
- Added offline Phase 2 gateway tests with fake provider SDK clients covering mock responses, fallback behavior, non-retryable failures, JSON parsing errors, provider request mapping, and tracing metadata extraction.
- Added `dev_plan/PHASE2_GATEWAY.md` and README notes documenting the Model Gateway boundary, mock-first provider strategy, fallback/error handling, and audit-vs-Commit-Log separation.
- Implemented Phase 3 in-memory Blackboard Service with run initialization, Working Memory writes, Belief State patch submission, permission/evidence/ticker/blocker validation, dot-path patch application, Commit Log creation, and objection/delegation lifecycle helpers.
- Added Phase 3 state transition tests covering Working Memory versus Belief State separation, patch validation failures, Commit Log behavior, unresolved objection blocking, active delegation blocking, and lifecycle unblock/retry behavior.
- Added `dev_plan/PHASE3_BLACKBOARD_SERVICE.md` and README notes documenting the in-memory repository boundary, patch submission rules, dot-path behavior, lifecycle semantics, and Phase 3 non-goals.
- Implemented Phase 4 agent runtime boundaries with default agent definitions, registry lookup, mock runner, and a MAF adapter placeholder that preserves the DoxAgent `AgentTask -> AgentResult` contract.
