- Added Phase 3.6 tests for module execution, document assembly, evidence requirements, workflow submission, research input round trips, and resume behavior, plus documentation in `dev_plan/PHASE_3_6_GLOBAL_RESEARCH_MODULE_INTEGRATION.md`.
- Hardened the real ReAct initialization path against live-model/provider drift by extracting fenced JSON, unwrapping nested `react_protocol` actions, retrying non-JSON/no-progress ReAct turns within budget, normalizing report-like `ResearchSection` payloads, treating required-tool gaps as audited warnings, and allowing Global Research sections to carry provider gaps without blocking document assembly.
- Added O1 expectation-construction normalization for draft expectation payloads and extra model fields, including conversion to `BlackboardPatch`/`ExpectationUnitDocument`-shaped data with audited provenance when external evidence is unavailable.
- Fixed ASTS real initialization by switching smoke tests to an ASTS research context, injecting compact GlobalResearchDocument context into downstream O1 tasks, adding explicit `ExpectationConstructionResult.proposed_patches` output-contract guidance, normalizing O1 patch targets/delegations/key variables/realized facts, and validating document 1 plus document 2 real smoke completion.
- Wired initialization workflow storage defaults to `DoxAgentSettings`, so postgres mode now automatically uses Postgres-backed Blackboard and checkpoint repositories while explicit test injections still override storage selection; added Supabase persistence smoke coverage gated by `DOXAGENT_RUN_REAL_DB_TESTS`.
- Configured local LangSmith tracing environment values for the `DoxAgent` project and added a project-level LangSmith Remote MCP entry without committing API-key headers.
- Trimmed ReAct/PromptAssembler agent-visible inputs, added node-specific initialization permissions and GlobalResearchContext filtering, and required O1 expectation construction to account for missing DoxAtlas narrative tool evidence.
- Moved C1/C3 global-research task instructions into internal task skills and changed external skill packages to on-demand ReAct text loading without runtime tool/output constraints.
- Cleaned mojibake from the new C1/C3 internal task skill prompt text and normalized ranges/separators to ASCII.
- Required Phase 17 real initialization smoke tests to use postgres persistence when enabled, and added debug-viewer visibility assertions so real smoke runs are queryable from the local Brief State Viewer instead of silently using memory storage.
- Reordered initialization so C1/C2/C3/O4 build Global Research I-IV in parallel, split O1 expectation generation into construction/detail phases with A1 construction review, moved Market Narrative to a post-belief-state update, and cleaned skill front matter runtime constraints.
- Restored Phase 17 real initialization smoke tests to honor the default `.env` LangSmith tracing settings now that the expired LangSmith API key has been replaced.
- Added workflow-side AgentResult acceptance auditing for parse/schema/write failures and cached per-agent Global Research section results in checkpoints so completed C1/C2/C3/O4 sections are not re-dispatched after a later section blocks.
- Disabled psycopg3 server-side prepared statements for Postgres/Supabase pooler connections so Blackboard, workflow checkpoint, debug viewer, and real persistence smoke paths avoid PgBouncer `DuplicatePreparedStatement` failures.
- Reworked A1 DoxAtlas audit into node-specific prompts, internal task skills, minimal per-node DoxAtlas tool permissions, and a stricter audit-shaped output contract with ReAct normalization for schema-stable `DoxAtlasAuditResult` payloads.
- Reworked A2 into a single-prompt lightweight public search and verification agent, removed its A2-specific internal skill path, added `anysearch.search` via the official AnySearch `/v1/search` API with environment-backed credentials, narrowed A2 to search-class tools, and stabilized `DelegatedRetrievalResult` normalization.
- Hardened real initialization recovery by routing O1 construction objections back through shell construction, prefetching missing narrative tool evidence before Working Memory writes, accepting strict field-review payloads, and converting direct known-events/monitoring documents into Blackboard patches.
- Added a local Blackboard eval contract under `eval/` with hard gates, LLM-as-judge rubrics, baseline/retest SOP, append-only eval records, and a run_id-based Brief State JSON exporter for future optimization loops.
- Added three local hard validators for Brief State review and eval export: evidence reference integrity, trajectory/tool-boundary compliance, and commit-log/state-mutation consistency.
- Switched the Phase 17 real initialization smoke/eval case from ASTS to MU with Micron-specific memory semiconductor research inputs while keeping real test execution opt-in.
- Updated the DashScope model configuration from `qwen3.6-flash` to `qwen3.7-plus` while keeping the provider and all other generation settings unchanged.
- Added Docker deployment support for DoxAgent with a Debug Viewer service bound to `127.0.0.1:8765`, isolated compose project naming, cache/tmp volumes, and a healthcheck suitable for the Tencent Cloud host; operational SSH/deployment notes live in `docs/server-ssh-deployment.md`.
